    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>NEW FOOD INSPECTION PROGRAM</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elsa Brenner</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brenner, Elsa</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New York State, responding to increase in food-borne illnesses and increase in imports, increases inspections and strengthens retail standards (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Responding to an increase in food-borne illnesses and the importation of food from abroad, the state has increased its safety efforts. A new law increases inspections and strengthens retail standards. As a result, supermarkets and other outlets will be subject to more rigorous inspection schedules and will be required to post their most recent inspection for the public to see. The law also requires each food store to post the results of its last inspection near each public entrance and to make these results available to the public upon request.</p>
        <p>Elsa Brenner</p>
      </block>
